snippet: Egypt’s highest court and its most senior generals dismissed President Mohamed Morsi’s order to restore the dissolved Parliament, reflecting dueling claims to the country’s emerging politics.
abstract: Egypt’s highest court and its most senior generals dismiss Pres Mohamed Morsi’s order to restore the dissolved Parliament, reflecting dueling claims to the country’s emerging politics; generals, backed by the court, argue that Morsi must respect legal precedents and the institutions of the state; Morsi, in turn, is calling on the generals to respect popular will that was expressed through free elections.

byline.contributor: Mayy El Sheikh and David D. Kirkpatrick contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Egypt’s highest court and its most senior generals dismissed President Mohamed Morsi’s order to restore the dissolved Parliament, reflecting dueling claims to the country’s emerging politics.
